704915f-a.text:
Hicks Street, at the N.W. corner of Orange Street, showing a house raned in 1886. It is said that Joel Bunce, the first Postmaster of Brodclyn, (about 1819) ocoupied it. It was also occupied for some years by the artist
Thomas Nast.
About 1886.
